dividually%20attend%20to%20any%20sick%20porpoises%20in%20a%20pod%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F12%2F26%2Fscience%2Forcas-killer-whales-veterinarians.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20Times%20report%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Southern%20Residents%20are%20the%20smallest%20of%20four%20groups%20of%20fish-eating%20killer%20whales%20found%20in%20the%20Pacific%20Ocean.%20The%20mammals%20were%20listed%20as%20endangered%20in%202005%20amid%20worsening%20pollution%2C%20depleted%20salmon%20supply%2C%20and%20increased%20boat%20danger.%20The%20animals%20have%20faced%20ongoing%20population%20troubles%20in%20the%20years%20since.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnly%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvitalsigns.pugetsoundinfo.wa.gov%2FVitalSignIndicator%2FDetail%2F32%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E75%20of%20the%20whales%20remain%3C%2Fa%3E%20even%20as%20conservationists%20fight%20to%20keep%20them%20alive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20Southern%20Resident%20swimming%20in%20the%20Salish%20Sea%20in%20September%20was%20the%20recipient%20of%20researchers'%20hard-fought%20innovation%20when%20a%20group%20of%20scientists%20at%20sea%20stumbled%20upon%20a%20putrid%20smell%20coming%20from%20the%20mammal's%20blowholes%2C%20the%20Times%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBad%20breath%20on%20a%20whale%20can%20be%20a%20sign%20of%20more%20significant%20health%20issues%2C%20scientific%20experts%20told%20the%20newspaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20stinky%20smell%20was%20cause%20for%20concern%2C%20the%20situation%20also%20offered%20researchers%20the%20serendipitous%20opportunity%20to%20try%20out%20a%20new%20%26quot%3Bbreath-collection%20drone%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20outlet%20reported%2C%20describing%20the%20device%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bflying%20petri%20dish%26quot%3B%20that%20can%20be%20maneuvered%20into%20an%20Orca's%20plume.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20device%20is%20still%20in%20development%2C%20but%20the%20whale's%20foul%20breath%20allowed%20researchers%20a%20chance%20to%20test%20the%20drone%20in%20the%20wild.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExperienced%20drone%20pilots%20have%20to%20launch%20the%20aircraft%20from%20small%20boats%20zooming%20through%20the%20water%20and%20navigate%20the%20drone%20to%20the%20exact%20right%20place%20above%20the%20whale%20to%20gather%20respiratory%20drops%2C%20which%20are%20full%20of%20telling%20information%20about%20the%20animal's%20health%2C%20according%20to%20The%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey've%20said%20a%20few%20times%20now%20that%20this%20is%2C%20technically%20speaking%2C%20the%20most%20complex%20mission%20they%20have%20ever%20flown%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr.%20Hendrik%20Nollens%2C%20the%20vice%20president%20of%20wildlife%20health%20for%20the%20San%20Diego%20Zoo%20Wildlife%20Alliance%2C%20who%20was%20on%20the%20expedition%2C%20told%20the%20outlet%20of%20the%20drone%20pilots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20putrid-smelling%20whale%20was%20identified%20as%20Tsuchi%2C%20a%2028-year-old%20known%20female%20in%20the%20pod%2C%20according%20to%20the%20newspaper%2C%20and%20the%20drone%20eventually%20helped%20researchers%20diagnose%20her%20with%20a%20condition%20akin%20to%20a%20bloody%20nose.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20drone%20technology%20is%20just%20one%20approach%20scientists%20have%20taken%20to%20treat%20Southern%20Residents%20in%20recent%20years.%20The%20National%20Oceanic%20Atmospheric%20Administration%20has%20worked%20with%20nonprofits%20to%20develop%20new%20techniques%2C%20including%20using%20aerial%20photography%20to%20keep%20abreast%20of%20the%20mammals'%20measurements%3B%20surveying%20whale%20fecal%20samples%20stolen%20from%20the%20water%3B%20and%20using%20a%20dart%20gun%20to%20administer%20antibiotics%20to%20a%20sick%20pod%20member%2C%20The%20Times%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20nonprofit%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wildorca.org%2Fstory%2Fhow-dogs-can-save-orcas%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWild%20Orca%3C%2Fa%3E%20even%20employs%20the%20use%20of%20a%20service%20dog%20who%20is%20trained%20in%20sniffing%20out%20whale%20feces%20to%20locate%20the%20animals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20told%20The%20Times%20that%20medical%20interventions%20alone%20won't%20save%20the%20Southern%20Residents.%20But%20the%20top-tier%20veterinary%20treatment%20on%20the%20water%20may%20buy%20the%20endangered%20animals%20some%20more%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Forca-whale-doctors-drones-dogs-treat-killer-patients-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703646504000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F658b8cf3ab6f2ebb11f70081%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Forca-whale-doctors-drones-dogs-treat-killer-patients-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20endangered%20Southern%20Residents%20are%20the%20smallest%20of%20four%20groups%20of%20fish-eating%20killer%20whales%20found%20in%20the%20Pacific%20Ocean.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22esnodgrass%40insider.com%20(Erin%20Snodgrass)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Forca-whale-doctors-drones-dogs-treat-killer-patients-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20don't%20completely%20trust%20Siddhant%20%3A%20Ananya%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703645918000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-106306463%2Cimgsize-45404.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fi-dont-completely-trust-siddhant-ananya-panday%2Farticleshow%2F106306510.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F106306510.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EAnanya%20Panday%2C%20promoting%20%26quot%3BKho%20Gaye%20Hum%20Kahan%2