roup%20of%2018%20Goffin's%20cockatoos%20over%20twelve%20days.%20During%20that%20period%2C%20they%20saw%20that%20seven%20of%20the%20birds%20dunked%20their%20hard%20crackers%20in%20water%20before%20eating%20them.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20certain%20birds%20held%20the%20cracker%20in%20water%20for%20a%20few%20seconds%20while%20other%20times%20they'd%20hold%20it%20for%20over%20half%20a%20minute%20%E2%80%94%20long%20enough%20to%20make%20the%20bottom%20soft%2C%20the%20researchers%20reported%20in%20the%20study.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EImagine%20holding%20your%20cookie%20in%20milk%20for%2030%20seconds%20before%20taking%20that%20delicious%20first%20bite%20%E2%80%94%20these%20birds%20certainly%20exhibited%20some%20self-control.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20birds%20also%20dunked%20banana%20and%20coconut%20chips%2C%20though%20this%20was%20less%20common.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20few%20reasons%20animals%20might%20dip%20their%20food%20in%20liquid%2C%20the%20study%20elaborated.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhighest-bungee-dunk-guinness-world-record-dunking-buscuit-tea-british-2016-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESoaking%20hard%20food%3C%2Fa%3E%20might%20change%20its%20texture%2C%20clean%20it%2C%20make%20it%20tastier%2C%20allow%20the%20bird%20to%20transport%20water%20for%20drinking%2C%20or%20be%20a%20way%20to%20drown%20and%20kill%20live%20prey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20case%2C%20though%2C%20the%20study's%20authors%20went%20through%20each%20of%20these%20possibilities%20and%20found%20that%20one%20made%20the%20most%20logical%20sense%20given%20the%20animals'%20unique%20environment%20%E2%80%94%20changing%20the%20food's%20texture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELouis%20Lefebvre%2C%20a%20biologist%20at%20McGill%20University%20who%20wasn't%20involved%20in%20the%20study%2C%20told%20The%20Times%20that%20this%20was%20%26quot%3Ba%20cool%20study.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20peculiar%20preference%20or%20common%20behavior%3F%3C%2F